        		<marginalia hand="Italian">
        			<language ident="LA">
            				<position book_orientation="0" place="head">
            			      		<marginalia_text>
            			      			P. Ceualerius, Ciuis Geneuensis, idemq[ue] magnus religionis,
            			      		</marginalia_text>
            				 	<person name="Pierre Chevalier"/>
            			      		<location name="Geneva"/>
            				</position>
        				<position book_orientation="0" place="right_margin">
        					<marginalia_text>
        						et Hebraica[e] lingua[e] professor, mihi sa[e]pè solebat dicere: ) Veni
        					</marginalia_text>
        				</position>
        				<position book_orientation="0" place="intext">
        					<marginalia_text>
        						) Domine: Eamus
        					</marginalia_text>
        				</position>
        				<position book_orientation="0" place="right_margin">
        					<marginalia_text>
        						in campos ad ridendu[m]. Cum primùm autem in campis essemus, 
        						statim sine
        					</marginalia_text>
        				</position>
        				<position book_orientation="0" place="intext">
        					<marginalia_text>
        						vlla causa ridebat Stentoricè.
        						Nec cessabat altissima exclamatione ridere, 
        					</marginalia_text>
        				</position>
        				<position book_orientation="0" place="right_margin">
        					<marginalia_text>
        						vt insanus; donec spiritus
        					</marginalia_text>
        				</position>
        				<position book_orientation="0" place="intext">
        					<marginalia_text>
        						deficeret. Ha-ha-ha. Hi-hi-hi. Ho-ho-ho. Ha-hi-ho. Nec 
        					</marginalia_text>
        				</position>
        				<position book_orientation="0" place="right_margin">
        					<marginalia_text>
        						finem ullum faciebat, donec
        					</marginalia_text>
        				</position>
        				<position book_orientation="0" place="tail">
        					<marginalia_text>
        						ferè rumperetur. Nunq[uam] vidi talem Pygma[e]um,
        						tantum agere in ridendo Gygantem.
        					</marginalia_text>
        				</position>
        			</language>
        			<translation>
        				Pierre Chevalier, citizen of Geneva and great professor of the Hebrew religion and language, 
        				often used to tell me: ) Come, master, Let's go to the countryside to laugh. But when arrived
        				in the fields, at once, without any reason, he would begin to howl with laughter.
        				And he wouldn't stop laughing in loud cries, as if unhealthy, until he ran out of breath. 
        				Ha-ha-ha. Hi-hi-hi. Ho-ho-ho. Ha-hi-ho. And he didn't stop, until he had
        				nearly burst. Never did I see such a dwarf seem like such a giant while laughing.
        			</translation>
        		</marginalia>
    		
